title: 3He Induced Nuclear Reactions on 237Np Targets

x4freetext: The parts housing the targets formed a Faraday cup,
which was connected to a current integrator to
determine the integrated charge of the 3He ions
The radionuclidic purity of the 237Np target was higher
than 99%. There were impurities of 238Pu and 239Pu
present in the target material, which contributed to
respectively. Thin and thick targets were prepared. The
thin targets were prepared by the evaporation of
0.1 mg/cm2 of neptunium on 6 or 50 mu-m thick aluminium
foils. The neptunium coated foils were stacked in a
pile and separated with 6 mu-m thick aluminium foils.
One thick neptunium target was made by piling three
50 mu-m thick aluminium foils, on which about 2 mg/cm2
of neptunium was first painted as neptunium nitrate
celluloze and then transformed to neptunium oxide by
thermal decomposition. In the thick target the
neptunium coated foils were also separated with 6mu-m
A total of ten irradiations were carried out: nine
with thin neptunium targets and one with a thick
Numb.       in MEV         of targets, mu-g/cm2
area of the detectors used varied from 150 to 300 mm2
